dct:description: Base concrete subclass of abstract data type; data value represented as  a list of values associated with an index; arrays have a dimension, and each dimension might map into some conceptual or physical space (the dimension type)
an opaque binary object. This is the lowest level kind of data object, essentially a bit stream that is meaningless without some context to interpret it. Physical types might specify number of bytes.
logical type, physical type might be single bit, -true- -false- string, -0- or -1- etc.
Base concrete subclass of abstract data type; value consists of a structured collection of attributes each with an associated dataType, Domain, and units of measure.
Base concrete subclass of abstract data type; a list of key-value pairs;
a blob that encodes a geospatial location
logical type; physical types might specify number of bytes, and value range
Base concrete subclass of abstract data type; value consists of a list of items each with its own dataType, and a specified delimiter that separates items.
a list of string values delimited with pipe (|) characters
a geometry that encodes a point in X-Y-Z
a geometry that encodes an X-Y point location
Base concrete subclass of abstract data type; includes basic computer programming data types e.g. xml data types.
skos:narrower: class/data-type/class/data-type/integer, class/data-type/boolean, class/data-type/real-number, class/data-type/string, class/data-type/datetime, class/data-type/date

dct:description: logical type, might be decimal, float, double, lots of possible low-level encoding schemes? (big endian, small endian?)
logical type for string; physical types might specify character encoding, number of bytes, etc.
a string that is restricted to be a member of labels from a controlled vocabulary
